               <head>Miscellaneous works on pilgrimage and prayer, 3 items (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089070  https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85106139 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068403">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous works on Arabic prayers for pilgrimage and other Islamic rites. 
Volume not dated; datable to late eighteenth century. 
Scribal naskh. 
Annotations in margins. 
Discontinuous Persian foliation. 
Lacking original binding. 
Plain Manila paper wrapper. 
Folios mostly bound; wormholes, cropped, water stains, some smudging. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_80x-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="54v">ff. 1v-54v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 80* a. 
</p>
                        <p>Abridged version extracting mainly the Arabic prayers from a treatise on pilgrimage rituals and prayers associated with the monuments of the Arabian city of Madīnah, written by the eminent Indian scholar and muḥaddis̲, <persName key="viaf_45690112" role="aut">ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Turk Dihlavī Bukhārī</persName> (d. 1052/1642). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_45690112">ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_45690112">عبد الحقّ دهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22253">Jaz̲b al-qulūb ilá diyār al-Maḥbūb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22253">جذب القلوب الىٰ ديار المحبوب</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_80x-item2">
                     <locus from="55r" to="62r">ff. 55r-62r </locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8044">Ibrāhīm ibn Dāʾūd al-Vāṣilī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8044">ابراهيم ابن داؤد الواصلى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 80* b. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Arabic prayers and eulogies in praise of the Prophet <persName key="person_97245226" role="subject">Muḥammad</persName> based on ḥadīs̲ sources, by <persName key="person_f8256" role="aut">Ibrāhīm ibn Dāʾūd al-Vāṣilī.</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_80x-item3">
                     <locus from="62v" to="65r">ff. 62v-65r </locus>
                     <author/>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 80* c. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of miscellaneous Arabic prayers briefly introduced with notes in Persian, compiled by an unnamed editor. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations on ritual prayers. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
